name: Ronnie McCoury
bio: Mandolin picker, singer with the Del McCoury band and the Travelin' McCourys

social_posts.post_text: Incredible lineup and a great cause this Sunday if anyone’s in Nashville! Come on out!

Lots of fun last night @bbowlnashville for @davidsden_nash a wonderful cause! Thanks to @krismyersdrums and @pdawgthedrummer for getting this together! @jerrydouglas @billevanssax @christiansedelmyer @danielkimbromusic @robmccoury
Merry Christmas from my family to yours!
I wrote a fun little Christmas song for the “Christmas on the Mountain” cd many years ago. Hope you’ve had a Bluegrass Christmas too!

Happy Birthday to the one and only @dollyparton  what’s not to love about her in life and song?  Had the honor of playing @dollywood on her live record in 1994!! She was amazing to listen to and be around for that moment in time.

Great visit today @cartervintageguitars with the man who built my mandolin Steve Gilchrist! I’ve been playing his mandolin since my uncle @daviddawggrisman laid it on me over 30 yrs ago! We’ve done it together!
Good time speaking with @herman_vince about @jerrygarcia for the @bluegrasshall exhibit!
Happy Birthday to dad and Heaven! I love you both so much!!
#tbt a great memory @martystuart house visiting with Earl & Louise

Happy Birthday Dr. Ralph Stanley! I had the pleasure of recording with Ralph Nov 2014. I’d seen him all my life playing the same festivals and halls. We really enjoyed the time we had on Down From the Mountain 6 week tour. I really miss his sense of humor he always made me laugh.  #legend  #the boywitha100yrdvoice

Happy 100th Birthday to the great Doc Watson! I have so many wonderful memories of talkin’, pickin’ and recording with him. One of my proudest musical moments was being nominated for a Grammy for Black Mountain Rag in 1999 with Doc, who “owned” that tune, on the Mac, Doc & Del recordings. 💙  #docwatson #boonenc

Another great night @theryman with @bobweir & the Wolf Bros with some old and new friends! Very proud of my daughter @emmamccouryphotography for capturing some great pix!! Thanks again to @mattbusch28
Happy 78th Birthday to Uncle Dawg @daviddawggrisman the man responsible for laying my #gilchristmandolin on me at 20 yrs old and inspiring me to this very day and always! Much love!
@thetravelinmccourys have some new merch! Check it out! Link in my bio. Limited amount of posters signed
Happy Birthday @sambushband my hero! The main man broke the mold when he made you! Love you lots…🎼🎂🎼
Happy 30th Anniversary to my sweetheart, my life @allisonmariemccoury ❤️ thank you for all the years and 3 wonderful children. Time flys when your in love.
Happy 100th Birthday to my @gibsonguitar #lloydloar she’s a beauty! 📸 @emmamccouryphotography
Happy 90th Birthday @willienelsonofficial I hope it’s a great day! Proud to have picked a few with you! #americanoriginal  #songwritershof  #countrymusichof #trigger
Happy Mothers Day to these wonderful mothers in my life! My mom @delmamccoury , Jean Bliss and my wife @allisonmariemccoury love them all! #strongwomen
Happy 20th Birthday to my sweet Emma! ❤️❤️love you!!
Another incredible “quick” day at @planet.bluegrass 50th in Telluride! So many great friends and so many I didn’t get to catch up with!  Last pix is by @onthedlphoto ❤️ Off to @weiserrivermusicfest
Happy Fathers Day! I got to spend it again on the road with dad and I know how lucky I am to do so! ❤️

Jesse was a true innovator on the mandolin. He created a style that was never heard before on the mandolin in our music. His smooth singing, along with his brother Jim, was impeccable. I don’t remember a time in my life without there music in it. RIP Jesse 💙

Another Giant in Bluegrass and Hero of mine has passed. As I said in my last post…Bluegrass mandolin had 3 stylists, Bill Monroe, Jesse McReynolds and this man Bobby Osborne! I can’t imagine how many hours of my life I’ve spent listening to him…since childhood! He was a wonderful friend and a true Legend.  RIP Bluegrass Great!
Big weekend @greyfoxbluegrass  with lots of friends! @delmccouryband @thetravelinmccourys @jerrydouglas @rbreiten @andyhallmusic @andyfalco
Had a great time with @lukasnelsonofficial yesterday. Wonderful fella! Check out his new release today Sticks and Stones! It’s great! 📸 @allisonmariemccoury @sophialeriassharp

So very proud to be nominated by @intlbluegrass in these categories! I never take these accolades for granted. We work hard at what we do and it’s nice to feel appreciated! Proud of dad @delmccouryband at 84yrs young and @thetravelinmccourys and @jasoncarterfiddle for the nominations! See you in Raleigh!
Thanks @redwood_ramble for a great time! Always good to see @joecravenmusic and some owls! @thecodykilby

So very proud of my hero’s entering the @intlbluegrass Hall of Fame @bluegrasshall this year! I’ve had many special times with these fellas. Countless listening hours. My heart is full ❤️❤️ congratulations @daviddawggrisman @sambushband
Happy Birthday @jerrygarcia enjoyed the few moments we had! This was at the Capitol Center in D.C. 1990 (?) I sold Jerry 2 banjos that night by way of  @daviddawggrisman 📸 @allisonmariemccoury
Well, @michaelclevelandfiddle is not only a great fiddler but is now taking up hair styling and of course he’s good at it!! 📸 @jstrausser.visuals Ossipee Valley Music Fest
Happy Birthday Bill Monroe, the Father of Bluegrass! Grateful to have had the time with my hero!! Proud to have been a Bluegrass Boy a couple nights!
This is gonna be fun!! Honored to be there with dad!
Wow! So this happened today, overwhelmed to have such a great time rehearsing with @ericclapton @bradleywalkermusic @sierradawnhull for @crossroadsguitarfestival tomorrow!
Really incredible weekend @crossroadsguitarfestival with @ericclapton @jerrydouglas @bradleywalkermusic @sierradawnhull  Dad & Clapton!
The always classic 📸 @jayblakesberg photos from @hardlystrictlybluegrass 🙏🏻
Congratulations to my son @josh_mccoury and @sophialeriassharp on getting engaged. I love you both and can’t wait for your life adventure!! ❤️❤️
Happy Birthday to @bobweir thanks for all the great music. Here’s a great pix from the @theryman with @martystuart
Big time in Texas @bloominbluegrassfestival
Here’s to my beautiful wife @allisonmariemccoury on her birthday! We’ve known each other for almost 40 years! From a teenager to a senior citizen! 😜 I love you sweetheart! ❤️

Very proud to be a small part of @billystrings and @michaelclevelandfiddle @recordingacademy nominated albums. These fellas are driving forces in the future of our music. Great to play with the wonderful and talented Terry Barber, a jewel of a fella!

location.city_name: Backstage at the Grand Ole Opry

social_posts.post_text: Photo dump from an incredible night celebrating Dads 20th Anniversary @opry with our friends!

We are delighted to announce the release of our McCoury Music debut, “Between the Lines,” on February 16th, 2024! ✨

The full length album is also now available for preorder on iTunes, don’t forget to check that out! Many hours of time, talent, and love have gone into this project from all involved, and we are truly thrilled and proud of the end result and cannot wait for y’all to hear the rest. Our tremendous thanks go to our band members Trevor, Conner, Bobby - our producer Ronnie McCoury, and special guests Del McCoury Jason Carter, Peter Rowan, Ronnie McCoury, Dennis Crouch, and Jerry Douglas. We’re still pinching ourselves to be a part of this team and to have made this music together! This album is a dream come true in many ways, and we’re awfully excited to hear what y’all think. 

#thepricesisters #albumrelease #newmusic #newreleases #2024 #bluegrass #rootsmusic #countrymusic #twinsisters #mccourymusic #debutalbum #delmccoury #ronniemccoury #jasoncarter #peterrowan #jerrydouglas #denniscrouch #musiccity #delyeah #heroes
Happy Birthday to @jormajestykaukonen  Hope you’ve had a great day!! #jackcasadybass #furpieceranch
Another great day in Music City! Rehearsal for Earl Scruggs tribute and then playing the @opry with @tonytrischka
Happy 100th Birthday to the great Earl Scruggs! He’s the reason my dad started playing bluegrass music therefore the reason I am!! We really miss his presence and sense of humor!!
